1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:07,650
Chapter 2 Cure Yourself of Excusitis, the Failure Disease People.

2
00:00:08,160 --> 00:00:11,810
As you think yourself to success, that's what you will study.

3
00:00:11,920 --> 00:00:12,689
People.

4
00:00:13,039 --> 00:00:20,930
You will study people very carefully to discover, then apply, success-rewarding principles to your life.

5
00:00:21,040 --> 00:00:23,330
And you want to begin right away.

6
00:00:23,839 --> 00:00:31,889
Go deep into your study of people, and you'll discover unsuccessful people suffer a mind-deadening thought disease.

7
00:00:32,160 --> 00:00:35,330
We call this disease excusitis.

8
00:00:35,600 --> 00:00:43,490
Every failure has this disease in its advanced form, and most average persons have at least a mild case of it.

9
00:00:43,920 --> 00:00:52,770
You will discover that excusitis explains the difference between the person who is going places and the fellow who is barely holding his own.

10
00:00:53,040 --> 00:00:59,090
You will find that the more successful the individual, the less inclined he is to make excuses.

11
00:00:59,520 --> 00:01:07,650
But the fellow who has gone nowhere and has no plans for getting anywhere always has a book full of reasons to explain why.

12
00:01:07,999 --> 00:01:14,049
Persons with mediocre accomplishments are quick to explain why they haven't, why they don't,

13
00:01:14,080 --> 00:01:16,689
why they can't, and why they aren't.

14
00:01:17,200 --> 00:01:21,170
Study the lives of successful people and you'll discover this.

15
00:01:21,359 --> 00:01:28,370
All the excuses made by the mediocre fellow could be but aren't made by the successful person.

16
00:01:28,880 --> 00:01:34,930
I have never met nor heard of a highly successful business executive, military officer,

17
00:01:34,960 --> 00:01:43,249
salesman, professional person, or leader in any field who could not have found one or more major excuses to hide behind.

18
00:01:43,440 --> 00:01:46,770
Roosevelt could have hidden behind his lifeless legs.

19
00:01:46,880 --> 00:01:49,889
Truman could have used no college education.

20
00:01:50,080 --> 00:01:53,889
Kennedy could have said, I'm too young to be president.

21
00:01:54,080 --> 00:01:57,889
Johnson and Eisenhower could have ducked behind heart attacks.

22
00:01:58,480 --> 00:02:03,730
Like any disease, excusitis gets worse if it isn't treated properly.

23
00:02:03,920 --> 00:02:08,369
A victim of this thought disease goes through this mental process.

24
00:02:08,719 --> 00:02:10,929
I'm not doing as well as I should.

25
00:02:11,119 --> 00:02:14,929
What can I use as an alibi that will help me save face?

26
00:02:15,119 --> 00:02:21,649
Let's see, poor health, lack of education, too old, too young, bad luck,

27
00:02:21,839 --> 00:02:31,329
personal misfortune, wife, the way my family brought me up, Once the victim of this failure disease has selected a good excuse,

28
00:02:31,359 --> 00:02:32,609
he sticks with it.

29
00:02:32,959 --> 00:02:39,010
Then he relies on the excuse to explain to himself and others why he is not going forward.

30
00:02:39,439 --> 00:02:46,609
And each time the victim makes the excuse, the excuse becomes embedded deeper within his subconsciousness.

31
00:02:46,879 --> 00:02:53,010
Thoughts, positive or negative, grow stronger when fertilized with constant repetition.

32
00:02:53,279 --> 00:02:58,769
At first, the victim of excusitis knows his alibi is more or less a lie.

33
00:02:59,040 --> 00:03:05,010
But the more frequently he repeats it, the more convinced he becomes that it is completely true,

34
00:03:05,119 --> 00:03:10,370
that the alibi is the real reason for his not being the success he should be.

35
00:03:10,879 --> 00:03:20,929
Procedure 1, then, in your individual program of thinking yourself to success must be to vaccinate yourself against excusitis,

36
00:03:21,040 --> 00:03:23,170
the disease of the failures.

37
00:03:23,920 --> 00:03:27,810
The four most common forms of excusitis.

